    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-07T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="156"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/830: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-07T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 7, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 7—12:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1539. Your 1113, 6th. Thank you for the <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>. It
                    will take a big chunk out of our problem. We have plenty of people to fill her,
                    but many cannot pay the fares. We will use the $20,000 in accordance with
                    instructions contained in your 1015, 28th.</p>
                <p>I presume your references to unoccupied space concerns the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Acadia</hi> and <hi rend="italic">St. John</hi>. We reported before that
                    people simply would not travel on these ships. I cannot say that I blame them.
                    Every other vessel which left these shores, including belligerent vessels,
                    carried as many people as it was found practicable to put on.</p>
                <p>We have warned all Americans still here that the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Washington</hi> may be their last opportunity for returning home and that
                    those who do not take advantage of this opportunity remain at their own
                    risk.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
